dict.string: Insert your MicroView and Programmer with Pin 1 in hole C7.
Insert your Red Jumper between points I9 and J17.
Insert your Green Jumper between points I10 and J18.
Insert your Blue Jumper between points I11 and J19.

We’re now going to use an RGB LED. 
Lets continue on to see how to identify the RGB LED’s pins...
Select your RGB LED and insert it into points J21, J22 (longest leg), J23 and J24.
Select a 330Ω resistor and insert it into points I17 and I21 of your breadboard.
Select a 330Ω resistor and insert it into points H18 and H23 of your breadboard.
Select a 330Ω resistor and insert it into points G19 and G24 of your breadboard.
Insert another Black Jumper between points F22 and X24.
Insert a Black Jumper between points A14 and X16.
Connect your MicroView to your computer’s USB Port.
Click on the “Run on Arduino” to put this code on your MicroView.
